  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-09-24",
    "date": "2021-09-20T18:44:56Z",
    "text": "Ranked Choice Voting Act\n\nThis bill requires each state to carry out elections for Senators and Representatives in Congress, including primary, special, and general elections, using a system of ranked choice voting. Under this system, each voter must rank the candidates for the office in order of the voter's preference."
